'\" t
.TH "ACTON\-RETRACE" "1"
.nh
.ad l
.ss \n[.ss] 0
.SH "NAME"
acton\-retrace \[em] Replay an on\-chain transaction locally for inspection
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBacton retrace\fR [\fIoptions\fR] \fIhash\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Download a transaction by hash and replay it locally in the TON sandbox.
.sp
\fBacton retrace\fR is useful for debugging failures, inspecting outgoing actions,
reviewing VM and executor logs, and comparing local replay results with the
original on\-chain execution.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.SS "Retrace Options"
.sp
\fIhash\fR
.RS 4
Transaction hash in hex format.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-net\fR \fInetwork\fR
.RS 4
Network to retrace from.
.sp
Without this flag, Acton tries mainnet first and then falls back to testnet.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-api\-key\fR \fIkey\fR
.RS 4
TonCenter API key for blockchain queries.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.RS 4
Show full cell hex in outgoing actions instead of only hashes.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-logs\-dir\fR \fIdir\fR
.RS 4
Write VM and executor logs into the specified directory.
.RE
.SS "Display Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-color\fR \fIwhen\fR
.RS 4
Control when to use colored output.
.sp
Possible values: \fBauto\fR, \fBalways\fR, \fBnever\fR
.RE
.SS "Project Options"
.sp
\fB\-\-manifest\-path\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Path to the \fBActon.toml\fR file to use for this invocation.
.sp
Use this when running the command outside the project directory or when the
manifest lives at a non\-default location.
.RE
.sp
\fB\-\-project\-root\fR \fIpath\fR
.RS 4
Path to the project root to use for configuration discovery and relative
defaults.
.sp
This conflicts with \fB\-\-manifest\-path\fR\&.
.RE
.SH "NETWORK AND API BEHAVIOR"
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'Without \fB\-\-net\fR, Acton tries mainnet and then testnet
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fBlocalnet\fR and \fBcustom:<name>\fR are not supported by the retrace backend
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'If no \fB\-\-api\-key\fR is provided, Acton throttles requests to reduce rate\-limit
failures
.RE
.sp
For library fallback lookups, retrace also supports \fBDTON_API_KEY\fR from the
environment.
.SH "OUTPUT"
The command prints:
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'network selection and state\-hash check status
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'transaction metadata and fee summary
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'compute and action phase summaries
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'decoded outgoing actions
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'additional full VM and executor logs when \fB\-\-logs\-dir\fR is used
.RE
.sp
When \fB\-\-logs\-dir\fR is set, Acton creates the target directory and writes
\fBvm.log\fR plus \fBexecutor.log\fR there.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB0\fR: The transaction was fetched and replayed successfully.
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fB1\fR: The transaction could not be found, network lookup failed, replay data
was incomplete, or local log files could not be written.
.RE
.SH "EXAMPLES"
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 1.\h'+01'Retrace with automatic network fallback:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton retrace 3c1b02a33390e596d83b306eab57b3f7271bc90e2e527ea4cafccfde25139d41
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 2.\h'+01'Force mainnet and use an API key:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton retrace 3c1b02a33390e596d83b306eab57b3f7271bc90e2e527ea4cafccfde25139d41 \-\-net mainnet \-\-api\-key YOUR_API_KEY
.fi
.RE
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04' 3.\h'+01'Save logs and show full outgoing cell bodies:
.sp
.RS 4
.nf
acton retrace 3c1b02a33390e596d83b306eab57b3f7271bc90e2e527ea4cafccfde25139d41 \-\-verbose \-\-logs\-dir .acton/retrace
.fi
.RE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fBacton help disasm\fR
.RE
.sp
.RS 4
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\fIRetrace command guide\fR <https://ton\-blockchain.github.io/acton/docs/commands/retrace>
